text.__SUMMARY__: Habenaria batesii is a species of plant in the family Orchidaceae. It is endemic to Cameroon. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests. It is threatened by habitat loss.
text.Sources: Pollard, B.J. & Darbyshire, I. (2004). "Habenaria batesii". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 2004: e.T46360A11046352. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.2004.RLTS.T46360A11046352.en. Retrieved 20 December 2017.
